<subSubSection id="5B55D499A8ABC0E520D01B553A69C172" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="type">
<paragraph id="2AEED83790FE3D759F50C84E782AA66C" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Type:</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB48DE41A832E5C0DAF5ED7DA45F44A2" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Mexico, Chihuahua, Municipio de Guadalupe y Calvo, Sierra Madre Occidental, N side of Cerro Mohinora, ca. 13 mi SW of Guadalupe y Calvo, open pine-fir woods with scattered spruce, nearly vertical, N facing rock wall, very moist with many bryophytes and rich herbaceous flora, 
<geoCoordinate id="C7F745CF75B8FB2701A4CC74DAF91451" degrees="25" direction="north" minutes="57" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="25.95">25°57'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="4327CDBE2FE1179161CB7557436AC4D4" degrees="107" direction="west" minutes="03" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="-107.05">107°03'W</geoCoordinate>
, 2950 m, 20 Aug 1988, 
<emphasis id="A1D0EF8AA3C0D33D026D108441768930" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">G.Nesom &amp; A.McDonald 6475</emphasis>
(holotype: TEX!; isotype: ARIZ!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F313385ED356076888C78DD4ADAA4451" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph id="BBF91F9717BBBEABB3FF619D595A8BD6" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18A24DDD2F0599F16E50FA8B20EA0314" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="60C3A5EC2307C5AB0EC4D9649433F4D4" bold="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Leaf</emphasis>
sheaths retrorsely scabrous to puberulent; collars ciliate; ligules abaxially puberulent. 
<emphasis id="DC20D900D4782C27FD6F4E5D939849A3" bold="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Lemma</emphasis>
keel and marginal veins proximally puberulent, between veins densely scabrous. 
<emphasis id="182B244DDCDCBFE0B0C737141FB32778" bold="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Lodicules</emphasis>
0.75 mm long, broadly ovate with a broad lateral lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3CB0A388C37491C60F159FD79A0ED663" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C9C75BC907C010EECF6116245F77833C" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7D7A815192436237CD668D8D56DEDE99" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">This subspecies is known only from the Sierra Mohinora, Chihuahua.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BBDA8200B2A137C8645AF361C9D86372" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="ecology">
