<subSubSection id="5546C2027027B94A18AB2156DE2D4181" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="specimens examined">
<paragraph id="2D38E78D19FC82C9050858E054D6C450" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Specimens examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="802C8A0230F57C560A81736212810D54" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Mexico. 
<emphasis id="965E9B3613C53082A1969C97B182DB05" bold="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Chihuahua:</emphasis>
Sierra Mohinora, near Cumbre Mohinora, 
<geoCoordinate id="07F4353F61E14403A72D2AED7044C9B4" degrees="25" direction="north" minutes="57" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="34" value="25.959446">25°57'34&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="2FAA141228471E6E10BF1D84A63390C8" degrees="107" direction="west" minutes="03" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="49" value="-107.063614">107°03'49&quot;W</geoCoordinate>
, 3250-3300 m, 13 Sep 2006, P.M.Peterson 20048, F.
<normalizedToken id="72647E4393694A92206FC471091AEEB3" originalValue="Sánchez-Alvarado">Sanchez-Alvarado</normalizedToken>
&amp; E.P.
<normalizedToken id="8FBEA233B913A5D2FA96AF67797D933B" originalValue="Gómez-Ruíz">Gomez-Ruiz</normalizedToken>
(US); ditto, 20049 (US); ditto, on summit, 10,000-12,000 ft [3050-3660 m], 16-17 Oct 1959, D.S.Correll 23177 &amp; H.S.Gentry (LL).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="893617E21A563217D7D155BA5BCBFD87" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2D6864B01714281E5C31A81D49AD9C84" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3FED87C15888213923E2E55BC68EAAE0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
When the second author visited the type locality in 2006, the habitat within 5 km of the peak was found to be quite disturbed by grazing and logging. The holotype was initially determined as 
<taxonomicName id="3243F7EDB6B879845DDFE4E274D31C3C" authorityName="Vasey" authorityYear="1888" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tracyi">
<emphasis id="4E32F8766E6D4C8809D104925D1CA60C" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Poa tracyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;vel. aff.&quot; by J.R &amp; C.G. Reeder in 1989).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
